      <body>
         <div>
            <head>Translated parts</head>
            <p xml:id="KR3j0080-start">
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:42:13.754+09:00">The Records say</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:42:48.91+09:00">that Sages toil and trouble for the world,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:42:51.087+09:00">devoting to it all their thoughts and energies,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:43:18.2+09:00">that this harasses their spirits,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:43:46.135+09:00">and affects their bodies.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:44:00.69+09:00">Consequently</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:44:26.647+09:00">Yao is reported to have been like shrivelled flesh,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:44:29.256+09:00">and Shun like dried food,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:45:08.126+09:00">whereas Chieh and Chou</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:45:16.14+09:00">had an embonpoint over a foot thick.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:46:26.639+09:00">One may well say that the bodies of Sages working hard for the world, and straining their minds for mankind,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:46:41.292+09:00">are weakened,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:46:47.222+09:00">and that they do not become stout or fat,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:47:29.176+09:00">One may well say[moved down!]</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:48:00.881+09:00">but to say that Yao</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:48:07.976+09:00">and Shun were like dried flesh or food,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:48:44.987+09:00">and that the embonpoint of Chieh and chou meaured over a foot</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:49:32.195+09:00"> is exaggerating.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:49:40.81+09:00">Fuke Huan of Qi said:</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:50:11.801+09:00">Before I had got hold of Guan Zhong, I had the greatest difficulties,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:50:55.34+09:00">after I had got him, everything was easy."</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:51:43.493+09:00">Duke Huan did not equal Yao and Shun,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:53:12.61+09:00">nor was Guan Zhong on a par with Yu and Xie.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:53:29.413+09:00">If Duke Huan found things easy,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:53:51.315+09:00">how could they have been difficult to Yao and Shun?</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:54:47.325+09:00">From the fact that Due Huan, having obtained the assistance of Guan Zhong, went on easily,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:55:05.555+09:00">we may infer that Yao and shun</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-16T23:55:47.305+09:00">after having secured the services of Yu and Xie</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:32:02.483+09:00">                                    cannot have been in difficulties.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:32:14.832+09:00">A man at ease has not many sorrows.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:32:28.218+09:00">Without sorrows he has no troubles,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:32:42.263+09:00">and if he is not troubled, his body does not wither.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:33:01.671+09:00">Shun found perfect peace brought about by Yao,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:33:24.318+09:00">both carried on the virtues of the preceding gerneration</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:34:26.047+09:00">and continued the pacification of the border tribes.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:34:37.327+09:00">Yao had still some trouble,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:43:27.335+09:00">but Shun could live at ease and unmolested.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:43:35.414+09:00">The Book of History says</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:44:21.537+09:00">that the Supreme Ruler gave repose,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:44:28.771+09:00">which refers to Shun,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:44:54.431+09:00">for Shun found peace everywhere, he continued the government</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:45:19.792+09:00">appointed intelligent officers, employed able men,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:45:55.517+09:00">and enjoyed a dignified repose, while the Empire was well administrated.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:46:14.096+09:00">Therefore Confucius exclaims:</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:46:29.096+09:00">Grand were Shun and Yu</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:55:56.683+09:00">possessing the Empire,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:55:56.934+09:00">did not much care for it.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:56:52.971+09:00">In spite</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:56:54.177+09:00">of this</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:57:20.114+09:00">Shun is said to have been dried up like preserved meat,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:57:49.972+09:00">as though he had been lacking in virtue, and had taken over a state in decay</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:58:28.468+09:00">like Confucius, who restlessly wandered about</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:58:45.11+09:00">seeking employment</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T00:58:56.207+09:00">having no place to rest in,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T01:03:15.643+09:00">no way to walk,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_025-4a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2019-11-17T01:04:06.064+09:00">halting and tumbling down on the roads,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_079-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="paulfahr" modified="2019-12-05T01:48:12.21+09:00">Is it true,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_079-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="paulfahr" modified="2019-12-05T22:44:45.373+09:00">Whenever people in their discussions</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_082-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="paulfahr" modified="2020-02-19T23:15:12.725+09:00">                                    Somebody asked:</seg>
            <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:29:13.206+09:00">The ancestor of the Confucian school</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:30:02.71+09:00">was Master Kong;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:30:15.042+09:00">the progenitor of the Mohist school</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:30:21.4+09:00">was Mo Di.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:03:01.26+09:00">Now, concerning the fact that the teachings of the Confucians are transmitted, whereas the methods of the Mohists are not,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:36:42.682+09:00">this is so because the moral teachings of the Confucians can be practiced,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:03:09.796+09:00">whereas the methods and discussions of the Mohists are difficult to implement.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:38:14.489+09:00">How can we proof this?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:57:55.922+09:00">The Mohist school (advocates) frugal burials</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T00:58:14.62+09:00">as well as worshipping the spirits;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:17:27.075+09:00">(these two) principles contradict (and even) oppose each other, preventing their implementation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:20:12.142+09:00">(therefore) it is only appropriate that (the Mohist teachings) are difficult to implement.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:20:41.209+09:00">How do they contradict each other?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:22:47.202+09:00">Given that spirits do not consist of dead people's essence,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:23:30.897+09:00">then (the benefit of) worshipping them would be uncertain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:25:01.473+09:00">Now the Mohist school claims that spirits do indeed consist of dead people's essence;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:26:07.667+09:00">to value the essence while despising the corpse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:27:59.868+09:00">this means to treat the spirit generously while disregarding (its former) body.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:38:46.58+09:00">If generosity and frugality to not accord with each other</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:39:42.361+09:00">and flowery words and real treatment (in one's treatment of the spirits) do not match,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:41:04.501+09:00">then (the spirits) will become angry and send down desaster,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:44:13.842+09:00">and even if one would worship [Huang Hui 黃暉 emendates you 右 for you 有] them,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:51:00.283+09:00">Human emotion longs for generous treatment but disdains frugal treatment,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:51:16.04+09:00">it is the same with the mind of the spirit.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:54:19.751+09:00">If somebody would use the methods of Master Mo</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:54:50.505+09:00">in order to serve the spirits and requests blessings,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T01:56:41.367+09:00">there would be little blessing but constant desaster.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:02:13.966+09:00">If one measures all by one,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:38:53.157+09:00">the Mohist school designed its methods</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:05:01.169+09:00">That they are discarded and not transmitted</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:52:55.438+09:00">all in this way</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:53:07.248+09:00">seems justified.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:54:56.614+09:00">'Mr Zuo's Tradition of the Chunqiu'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:55:48.631+09:00">came out of Master Kong's wall.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:39:24.984+09:00">During the time of the Filial Martial Emperor</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:57:58.781+09:00">King Gong of Lu pulled down the teaching hall of Master Kong in order to rebuild it into a palace,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:58:31.234+09:00">he thereby got hold of a lost 'Chunqiu' in thirty chapters,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:39:57.904+09:00">this was 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)'.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T02:59:29.822+09:00">Gongyang Gao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:43:20.163+09:00">Guliang Zhi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:02:15.976+09:00">everybody according to his own views,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:42:34.637+09:00">but only 'Mr Zuo's Tradition' was close (to the time when the 'Chunqiu' was made) and captured its historical facts.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:04:57.508+09:00">How can we proof this?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:06:33.973+09:00">The 'Records of Ritual' were made in Master Kong's hall,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:06:45.928+09:00">and His Lord the Grand Scribe</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:07:34.907+09:00">was a comprehensively educated man of the Han,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:08:02.248+09:00">the words of Mr Zuo accord with those to works,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:43:03.43+09:00">whereas those of Gongyang Gao</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:08:18.375+09:00">Guliang Zhi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:43:32.046+09:00">and Mr Humu do not.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:43:40.503+09:00">Further, those scholars were removed from Master Kong's (time),</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:44:28.169+09:00">to be removed in time is not as good as being close (to somebody) in time,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:10:33.184+09:00">to here of (somebody) is not as good as to see him (personally).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:12:56.127+09:00">Liu Zizheng [i.e. Liu Xiang] studied 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)' just for fun</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:13:37.613+09:00">and (his houshold's) servants as well as his wife and children all recited it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:14:30.428+09:00">During the time of the Illustrious Martial Emperor</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T03:14:32.425+09:00">Chen Yuan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T04:12:12.452+09:00">and Fan Sheng repeatedly handed in writings</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T06:25:45.042+09:00">putting forward (a number of) passages supporting and refuting it [sc. the Zuozhuan];</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T04:33:49.231+09:00">(Chen) Yuan and (Fan) Sheng</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:45:47.882+09:00">thereupon 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)' was established [sc. as part of the official curriculum at the university in Luoyang].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T04:38:16.875+09:00">After a while, Fan Sheng was dismissed from office because of an offense.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:37:06.715+09:00">were great talents of the empire,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:09:26.489+09:00">they discussed right and wrong</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T06:26:15.42+09:00">with the utmost vigour.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:51:13.053+09:00">Chen Yuan's word were accepted [Liu Pansui 劉盼遂 proposes to emandate na 納 for ne 訥],</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:16:58.11+09:00">and Fan Sheng's memorials were refuted;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:46:28.131+09:00">that 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)' captures the facts</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:15:58.893+09:00">is (therefor) obvious.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:27:14.224+09:00">To talk a lot about strange things</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:29:26.412+09:00">highly contradicts (the fact that) Master Kong did not discuss strange things and brute force.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-03-25T05:34:29.837+09:00">'The Chunqiu of Mr Lü' is also like this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:20:00.462+09:00">The 'Discourses of the Many States'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:29:40.146+09:00">is the outer tradition of 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)'.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:47:17.753+09:00">Mr Zuo wrote a commentarial tradition for the classic [sc. the 'Chunqiu'],</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:47:28.191+09:00">(but) its words are still cursory.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:26:29.902+09:00">Therefor he again selected and wrote down the words of the 'Discourses of the Many States' in order to flesh them out.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:29:50.858+09:00">Therefor 'Mr Zuo's (Tradition)'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:26:58.414+09:00">and the 'Discourses of the Many States'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:48:12.813+09:00">are thruthfull writings of today's Confucianists.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0080_tls_083-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#paulfahr" modified="2020-04-23T02:42:08.636+09:00">and Mr Humu all wrote a commentarial tradition for the 'Chunqiu',</seg>
                </p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
